This was the third session by the dynamic duo of Chet Baker and Art Pepper, the first two having been an unparalleled success. Baker and Pepper had an instinctive relationship that resulted in exceptional interplay.

This thoroughly enjoyable and often highly dynamic LP is recommended for the bebop connoisseur as well as the mainstream enthusiast.

Recording: October 1956 in mono
